\[
T = \left[\frac{v_o}{v_{oT}}\right]_{v_1=v_2=0} =\frac{(v^-_T)(-A_d)}{v_{oT}}
\]
\\
\[
T = \frac{\left(\frac{v_{oT}(R//R)}{R_f + R//R}\right)(-A_d)}{v_{oT}}
\]
\\
\[
T = \frac{(R/2)(-A_d)}{R_f + R/2} = \frac{-R.A_d}{R + 2.R_f} 
\]
\\

Para la ganancia a lazo cerrado $A_{vf}$, se procede de la siguiente manera, aplicando teorema de superposición para las ganancias a lazo abierto:\\

\[
A_{v1} = \left[\frac{v_o}{v_1}\right]_{v_2=v_{oT}=0} =\frac{(v^-_1)(-A_d)}{v_1} = \frac{\left(\frac{v_1(R//R_f)}{R + R//R_f}\right)(-A_d)}{v_1}
\]
\\
\[
A_{v1} = \frac{(R//R_f)(-A_d)}{R + R//R_f} = \frac{\frac{R.R_f}{R+R_f}(-A_d)}{R + \frac{R.R_f}{R+R_f}} = \frac{R_f(-A_d)}{R + 2R_f}
\]
\\
\[
A_{vf1} = \frac{A_{v1}}{1-T} = \frac{\frac{R_f(-A_d)}{R + 2R_f}}{1-\frac{-R.A_d}{R + 2.R_f}} = -\frac{R_f.A_d}{R + 2.R_f+R.A_d}
\]
\\
\[
A_d \to \infty : \hspace{1cm}
A_{vfi1} = -\frac{R_f}{R}
\]
\\

\[
A_{v2} = \left[\frac{v_o}{v_2}\right]_{v_1=v_{oT}=0} =\frac{(v^-_2)(-A_d)}{v_2} = \frac{\left(\frac{v_2(R//R_f)}{R + R//R_f}\right)(-A_d)}{v_2} = \frac{R_f(-A_d)}{R + 2R_f}
\]
\\
\[
A_{vf2} = \frac{A_{v2}}{1-T} = \frac{\frac{R_f(-A_d)}{R + 2R_f}}{1-\frac{-R.A_d}{R + 2.R_f}} = -\frac{R_f.A_d}{R + 2.R_f+R.A_d}
\]
\\
\[
A_d \to \infty : \hspace{1cm}
A_{vfi2} = -\frac{R_f}{R}
\]
\\


Tal que se puede escribir la expresión de la salida ideal a lazo cerrado:
\\
\[
v_{ofi} = A_{vfi1}.v_1 + A_{vfi2}.v_2 = -\frac{R_f}{R}(v_1 + v_2)
\]
\\

Y su forma real (no ideal):
\\
\[
v_{of} = A_{vf1}.v_1 + A_{vf2}.v_2 = -\frac{R_f.A_d}{R + 2.R_f+R.A_d}(v_1 + v_2)
\]
\\


